        "body": "Given that the `PDFDocumentLoadingTask.destroy()`-method is documented as being asynchronous, you thus need to await its completion before attempting to load a new PDF document when using the global `workerPort`.\r\nIf you don't await destruction as intended then a new `getDocument`-call can remain pending indefinitely, without any kind of indication of the problem, as shown in the issue.\r\n\r\nIn order to improve the current situation, without unnecessarily complicating the API-implementation, we'll now throw during the `getDocument`-call if the global `workerPort` is in the process of being destroyed.\r\nThis part of the code-base has apparently never been covered by any tests, hence the patch adds unit-tests for both the *correct* usage (awaiting destruction) as well as the specific case outlined in the issue.",
        "created_at": "2023-08-12T16:39:22Z",
        "updated_at": "2023-08-13T11:27:42Z",
        "closed_at": "2023-08-13T10:18:28Z",
